# Premast CMS Client Site — Cursor Rules

## Project Type
This is a Premast CMS client site — a Next.js app powered by @premast/* packages.

## CRITICAL — Do Not Break

- NEVER import mongoose in "use client" files — it's server-only
- NEVER create individual API route files (e.g., app/api/pages/route.js) — use the catch-all at app/api/[...route]/route.js
- NEVER edit files in node_modules/@premast/* — changes are lost on install
- NEVER remove webpack aliases from next.config.mjs — breaks admin theme
- NEVER remove transpilePackages from next.config.mjs — breaks @premast/* JSX
- ALWAYS keep site.config.js and puck.config.js in sync when adding blocks
- ALWAYS add "use client" to files using React hooks, browser APIs, or Ant Design components
- ALWAYS use CSS variables (var(--theme-*)) instead of hardcoded colors

## File Purposes

- site.config.js → Central config (blocks + plugins). Server-safe, has mongoose access.
- puck.config.js → Client-safe Puck config. Same blocks but NO mongoose. Used in "use client" editor components.
- middleware.js → Auth middleware. Protects /admin routes.
- theme/tokens.js → Design tokens (CSS variables for colors, fonts).
- theme/antd-theme.js → Ant Design theme config for admin panel.
- theme/puck.css → Puck editor theme overrides.
- app/api/[...route]/route.js → Catch-all API route. Do NOT add separate route files.

## Import Rules

- Use @/ alias for project files: import { siteConfig } from "@/site.config"
- Use package names for @premast imports: import { createSiteConfig } from "@premast/site-core"
- In "use client" components: import { puckConfig } from "@/puck.config" (NOT site.config.js)

## Adding a New Block

1. Create components/puck/MyBlock.jsx (with fields, defaultProps, render)
2. Create components/puck/MyBlock.module.css (use var(--theme-*) for colors)
3. Add MyBlock to site.config.js blocks AND categories
4. Add MyBlock to puck.config.js blocks AND categories
5. Restart dev server

## Adding a Plugin

1. npm install @premast/site-plugin-xyz
2. Import and add to site.config.js plugins array
3. Add "@premast/site-plugin-xyz" to next.config.mjs transpilePackages

## CSS Rules

- Use CSS Modules (.module.css) for component styles
- Use var(--theme-accent), var(--theme-text), var(--theme-surface), etc.
- Never hardcode colors — breaks theming

## Mongoose Pattern

Always use HMR-safe pattern for custom models:
```
export const MyModel = mongoose.models.MyModel ?? mongoose.model("MyModel", mySchema);
```

## Auth

- JWT in HTTP-only cookies
- /admin/setup → create first admin (one-time)
- /admin/login → login page
- Roles: super_admin, editor

## Database Models

- Page → standalone pages (Home, About)
- ContentType → content blueprints (Blog Article, Service)
- ContentItem → individual content pieces
- Global → header, footer
- User → admin users
